Package com.marcosavard.commons.util

Class StringUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.marcosavard.commons.util.StringUtil
  • public class StringUtil
extends java.lang.Object
    A utility class that provides useful methods that handle strings. It includes methods to predicate whether a string is null or empty, to pad strings with blanks, to remove quotes from strings, to strip accents from a string.
    Author:
    Marco

      • stripBlanks

        public static java.lang.String stripBlanks​(java.lang.String text)
        Return a string in which all the blanks (whitespaces and tabs) of the text parameter are stripped off. For instance, stripBlanks("hello world") returns "helloworld".
        Parameters:
        text - the original String, that may contain characters with blanks.
        Returns:
        the same String, but without blanks
